notesStmt.note: Title from colophon (f. 210r); alternate title Ācāraratna also from colophon.
210 leaves foliated 1-210, upper left and lower right verso.
Mistakes covered over in yellow or blacked out; some corrections and additions in margins; significant syllables, words, or phrases highlighted in red throughout.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Compendium of Hindu laws (dharma) functioning as an instructional manual for priests to perform different rites and ceremonies, including death rituals and procedures, fasting observances (vratas), and domestic rituals.

msItem.title: Ādnīkaprakaraṇa
आह्निकप्रकरण
msItem.colophon: Colophon: iti śrīmannārāyaṇabhaṭṭātmajaśrīmadrāmakṛṣṇabhaṭṭasutalkṣmaṇabhaṭṭakṛtāvācāraratne ādnīkaprakaraṇaṃ samāptaṃ śubharamastu // śrīrāmacaṃdrāyanamaḥ (f. 210r).
